    <h1 class="mb-6">AI Search Visibility for Solicitors</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Law firms that rank well on Google are regularly absent from AI search answers. In our UK testing, the legal sector scored zero on several key AI visibility signals.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The reason: AI platforms evaluate trust differently from Google. They cross-reference the SRA register, directory listings, editorial mentions, and client reviews. A law firm that only exists on its own website has one voice. AI needs many.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">For the full sector analysis, see our <a href="/who-we-help/solicitors/" class="link">solicitors sector page</a>. For the methodology behind our testing, see our <a href="/research/methodology/" class="link">methodology</a>.</p>
